WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:09.600 --> 00:00:19.680
Place 2 eggs, vanilla sugar (10 g) and 280 g of sugar into a bowl.

00:00:26.180 --> 00:00:29.480
Mix them until fluffy.

00:00:34.100 --> 00:00:37.360
Add 150 g of butter and mix again.

00:00:38.740 --> 00:00:43.980
Combine 250 g of flour and 1 baking powder (10 g).

00:00:45.040 --> 00:00:50.200
And add 5 table spoons of dark cocoa.

00:01:14.080 --> 00:01:17.340
Prepare 2,2 dl of milk.

00:01:17.340 --> 00:01:21.460
And then alternately add a little bit of flour mixture and milk to eggs.

00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:27.200
Grease baking tray with butter. I used round one, 30 cm in diameter.

00:01:27.880 --> 00:01:32.780
Pour in half of dough mixture.

00:01:33.800 --> 00:01:39.120
Bake at 180 degrees.

00:01:39.580 --> 00:01:46.140
Meanwhile grate 150 g of dark chocolate.

00:01:46.520 --> 00:01:50.960
When the first biscuit is baked, bake another one the same and move the first one to the serving tray like shown.

00:01:54.740 --> 00:02:00.440
Make sure you lift the biscuit with a knife a little bit around and around to avoid any accidents.

00:02:01.620 --> 00:02:08.900
Melt 4 teaspons of sugar in 1 dl of water and 1/2 dl of rum.

00:02:15.160 --> 00:02:21.840
With half of it moisten the first part of biscuit.

00:02:31.120 --> 00:02:38.380
Firmly mix 1/2 L of cream.

00:02:38.380 --> 00:02:42.320
Optionally add 1/2 of packaging of gelatine (the instant one that does not have to be melted).

00:02:42.320 --> 00:02:47.380
Add grated dark chocolate and 1 vanilla sugar.

00:02:58.920 --> 00:03:05.080
Spread cream evenly.

00:03:41.120 --> 00:03:45.400
Now moisten the other half of biscuit as well.

00:03:46.600 --> 00:03:53.260
And place it on top of the cream.

00:04:00.520 --> 00:04:05.700
Melt 3 bars of dark chocolate (50 g) with 3 tablespoons of oil.

00:04:06.760 --> 00:04:11.300
Pour it over the cake and spread evenly.

00:04:13.120 --> 00:04:19.020
Decorate the cake. You can save some of the cream used inside of the cake for decorating.

